";s:26:"www.gandtgaragedoors.co.uk";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:39:"garage door keeps running after closing";s:4:"slug";s:39:"garage-door-keeps-running-after-closing";s:5:"title";s:46:"Common Broken Garage Door Problems And Repairs";s:3:"alt";s:17:"a1a overhead door";s:3:"url";s:87:"https://www.a1aoverheaddoors.com/wp-content/uploads/A1A-Overhead-Door-LFA-Picture-3.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTOzlT8-hrEV228aq0qEzgEtY8RZvjnnzHxhA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1333;s:6:"height";i:1999;s:6:"source";s:93:"https://www.a1aoverheaddoors.com/blog/2018/04/common-broken-garage-door-problems-and-repairs/";s:6:"domain";s:24:"www.a1aoverheaddoors.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:62:{i:0;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:1;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:2;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:3;s:28:"This infrared sensor passes.";i:4;s:28:"The limit switch is not set.";i:5;s:63:"When the garage door reaches the open or closed limit it stops.";i:6;s:114:"If your garage door keeps opening by itself after you closed it you may have to adjust your closed limit settings.";i:7;s:134:"The garage door will close completely and then continue moving in the reverse direction leaving you with a partially open garage door.";i:8;s:25:"Click to see full answer.";i:9;s:39:"Garage door opener motor keeps running.";i:10;s:101:"I have an older opener and wanted to adjust the height so I could get a few more inches of clearance.";i:11;s:45:"There were 2 adjustment knobs open and close.";i:12;s:91:"When the door was in the open position I turned the open knob and it moved up a few inches.";i:13;s:52:"Then closed the door and it didnt close all the way.";i:14;s:111:"My garage door has two sensors either of which can cause the door to open immediately after apparently closing.";i:15;s:156:"A force-sensitive switch that detects if the motor torque is excessive typically tripped by incorrect adjustment or by leaving a solid object in the way of.";i:16;s:77:"Your garage door is programmed to travel a certain distance before it closes.";i:17;s:138:"If it closes before that distance has been traveled it thinks something is wrong and it reopens to help prevent any damage or safety risk.";i:18;s:34:"But changes in weather conditions.";i:19;s:110:"When you open your garage door and the motor wont stop running there might be a problem with the limit switch.";i:20;s:66:"This problem can be very annoying because it makes a lot of noise.";i:21;s:65:"The limit switch is the one that controls the travel of the door.";i:22;s:71:"It tells the motor that lowers and lifts the door when to stop running.";i:23;s:26:"Failure to Close Properly.";i:24;s:119:"Whether the door is not closing all the way or is closing and then immediately opening again you have a security issue.";i:25;s:78:"You need to know that your door will close and stay closed when you ask it to.";i:26;s:121:"In these situations start by ensuring that there are not any items blocking the sensors at the bottom of the garage door.";i:27;s:74:"Garage door re opens after closing 13953914D Craftsman Garage door opener.";i:28;s:30:"Report This by Manage My Life.";i:29;s:73:"My garage door goes all the way down and re opens when it hits the floor.";i:30;s:124:"I have tried adjusting the down force but can not seem to get it rightNo flashing lights and the sensors seem to be aligned.";i:31;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:32;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:33;s:159:"If you find that your garage door opener is running but your garage door isnt opening there are two possible problems that could be affecting your garage door.";i:34;s:49:"The first problem could be with the motor itself.";i:35;s:57:"Your garage door opener could have a broken part or gear.";i:36;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:37;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:38;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:39;s:29:"Try to close the garage door.";i:40;s:130:"If it still automatically begins to reverse or open back up turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn and test it again.";i:41;s:32:"Continue turning the down screw.";i:42;s:118:"The first step is to locate the emergency release and disengage it do it only if the garage door is completely closed.";i:43;s:59:"Detach the opener by pulling the emergency handle downward.";i:44;s:62:"The next step is to attempt to open your garage door manually.";i:45;s:79:"This will determine if the issue is connected to the door itself or the opener.";i:46;s:288:"After following these tips if you are still having problems getting the door to close and you need to leave your house you can override the sensors by holding down the wall button until the door is all the way down or you can put your door on manual by disconnecting it from the operator.";i:47;s:94:"If your Garage Door Opener will not close the garage door then there may be a very simple fix.";i:48;s:61:"This video will show you a simple way to troubleshoot the au.";i:49;s:22:"Door Keeps on Closing.";i:50;s:31:"GDZone Sat Jun 30 2018 1118 am.";i:51;s:104:"To check the balance on your door you pull the red emergency cord on the opener when the door is closed.";i:52;s:56:"Then lift the garage door until it is about 12 way open.";i:53;s:44:"Let go of the door and make sure your hands.";i:54;s:69:"To unlock your garage door opener push the lock button for 5 seconds.";i:55;s:79:"Once you push this button the light on the garage door opener will flash twice.";i:56;s:77:"Once you see the double flash press the control button on the remote control.";i:57;s:98:"If this doesnt fix your problem then the problem is more than likely the safety reversing sensors.";i:58;s:110:"One or more of these reasons is likely responsible for your garage door closing partially but not all the way.";i:59;s:28:"Something blocking the door.";i:60;s:64:"Though this problem should be obvious it shouldnt be overlooked.";i:61;s:95:"If theres something blocking the door from closing all the way a full close will be impossible.";}}